# URL of your n8n webhook / Netlify Function proxy
# The Airtable token lives server-side — never put it here
# The bundled netlify/functions/api.ts proxy serves same-origin at /api, so "/api" works both
# locally (via `netlify dev`) and once deployed.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api

# --- Server-side only (set these in the Netlify site's Environment Variables UI, not here) ---
# AIRTABLE_TOKEN=pat...
# AIRTABLE_BASE_ID=app...
